učenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].
==History== In [[history|historical records]], the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1329 as a parish and a castle (1329 ''castrum Dyun'''' '''villa sub eodem castro'', 1393 ''Dyen'', ''Dyuen'', 1497 ''Dywyn'', 1473 ''Dewen''). Many noble families ruled the village and lived in the castle: Tomay, Lossonczy, [[Balassa]], [[Zichy]]. In 1575 the fortress was occupied by [[Ottoman Empire|Turks]] up to 1593. In 1604, it passed to nobles [[Bocskay]], and after to Balassa family again. In 1674, the castle was destroyed by General Strassoldo.
